Exactly!What are the implications of using partcleboard? It appears to me that it is not necessary to grow trees greater than a few inches diameter to satisfy IKEA needs.So, guess what? IKEA, perhaps unwittingly, supports forest mgt that entails clearing young forests long before they are mature, and thus less valuable as wildlife habitat.Such juvenile trees are far cheaper compared to large mature trees. That also takes away the incentive for forest owners to grow mature forests, which helps landowners pay the cost of owning the forest land.Casual observers don't realize this, but corporations and enviros do. That is one of the few points the two agree on - try to starve the forest owners to death, or at least until they must relinquish ownership of their land.Want to help sustainable forestry? Use SOLID WOOD - NOT THE PARTICLEBOARD JUNK.



