I don't understand the need to keep buying new things when so much is out there for free/cheaper and often better quality. So much furniture and household goods are thrown away in house clearances but would be of use to others. I stopped shopping at ikea when I realised second hand solid wood furniture was cheaper and looked much nicer. I live in a student area and every year new students are out buying plastic washing up bowls, pans and kettles which are in abundance on freecycle. When we have so much stuff available we don't need to keep producing more in the shops as where does it all go? Household waste to the tip in our city has doubled in 3 years apparently and that's unrecyclable items!



